---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../components/CtaBanner.astro';
import { personSchema } from '../lib/schema';

const schema = personSchema({
  name: 'Quinn Schwartz',
  jobTitle: 'Founder, Schwartz Marketing Lab',
  description:
    'Quinn Schwartz is a former journalist and AEO strategist who built Schwartz Marketing Lab to help B2B companies get found in AI search and modern discovery systems.',
});
---

<Layout
  title="About Schwartz Marketing Lab — AEO & Content Strategy Agency"
  description="Quinn Schwartz is a former journalist and AEO strategist who built Schwartz Marketing Lab to help B2B companies get found in AI search and modern discovery systems."
  canonicalPath="/about"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>A better kind of agency.</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Schwartz Marketing Lab was built on a simple premise: the way people find information has changed faster
        than most agencies have adapted. Discovery now happens across Google, ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Claude — not
        just one search box — and the strategy behind getting found needs to reflect that.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>A journalism background, applied to discoverability</h2>
      <p>
        Before founding Schwartz Marketing Lab, Quinn Schwartz worked as a journalist, writing more than 1,000
        bylines and earning Keystone Press awards along the way. That background shapes how the agency approaches
        content: every piece is built to hold up under the same scrutiny a journalist would apply — is this
        accurate, is this specific, does this actually add information the reader didn't already have.
      </p>
      <p>
        That standard turns out to matter more, not less, in an AI search environment. Systems like ChatGPT and
        Perplexity reward content that demonstrates real expertise and penalize content that simply restates
        what's already been said elsewhere. A journalism background is, in practice, training for exactly the kind
        of writing AEO rewards.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Why "AEO agency" and not something broader</h2>
      <p>
        Schwartz Marketing Lab doesn't try to be a full-service marketing agency, and intentionally doesn't claim
        categories like paid media or product-led growth that other firms own more credibly. The focus is
        narrower and more specific: helping B2B brands become discoverable and citable across both traditional
        search and AI answer engines, through SEO, AEO, content strategy, and authority building working together
        rather than as separate line items.
      </p>
    </section>

    <RelatedLinks
      heading="What this looks like in practice"
      links={[
        {
          label: 'AEO & GEO',
          href: '/services/answer-engine-optimization',
          description: 'Getting found in ChatGPT, Perplexity, and AI Overviews.',
        },
        {
          label: 'Content Systems',
          href: '/services/content-systems',
          description: 'Content built to compound, not just to publish.',
        },
        {
          label: 'Executive Authority',
          href: '/services/executive-authority',
          description: 'LinkedIn and owned-channel authority building.',
        },
      ]}
    />

    <CtaBanner
      heading="Want to talk through your specific situation?"
      body="Book a call and we'll walk through where your brand stands today and where the highest-leverage opportunities are."
    />
  </div>
</Layout>
